    <descriptionSet>
      <description>The outlaw Jesse James has been depicted in story and song since his murder in 1882 at the hands of Robert Ford. The lyrics used in songs are mostly biographical  and detail his and his gang’s exploits. In many of these stories he is portrayed as a “Robin Hood” of the west which only served to increase his popularity with average citizens and build his status as a legend of the Wild West.</description>
    </descriptionSet>
